.TH "vc-frame" "1" "2026-06-10" "vc-frame 0.45.3"
.SH NAME
\f[B]vc\-frame\f[R] \- run VC Frame
.SH DESCRIPTION
VC Frame is a vibecrafted runtime and terminal workspace aimed at
developers, operators, AI\-agent workflows, and anyone who loves the
terminal.
At its core, it is a terminal multiplexer (similar to tmux and screen),
but this is merely its infrastructure layer.
.PP
VC Frame includes a layout system, and a plugin system allowing one to
create plugins in any language that compiles to WebAssembly.
.PP
To list currently running sessions run:
\f[CR]vc\-frame list\-sessions\f[R] To attach to a currently running
session run: \f[CR]vc\-frame attach [session\-name]\f[R]
.SH OPTIONS
Run \f[CR]vc\-frame \-\-help\f[R] to see available flags and
subcommands.
.SH CONFIGURATION
VC Frame looks for configuration file in the following order:
.IP "1." 3
the file provided with \f[I]\[en]config\f[R]
.IP "2." 3
under the path provided in \f[I]VC_FRAME_CONFIG_FILE\f[R] or
\f[I]ZELLIJ_CONFIG_FILE\f[R] environment variable
.IP "3." 3
the default location (see FILES section)
.IP "4." 3
the system location
.PP
Run \f[CR]vc\-frame setup \-\-check\f[R] in order to see possible issues
with the configuration.
.SH LAYOUTS
Layouts are yaml files which VC Frame can load on startup when
\f[I]\[en]layout\f[R] flag is provided.
By default VC Frame will load a layout called \f[CR]default.yaml\f[R],
but this can be changed by using the
\f[CR]default_layout: [LAYOUT_NAME]\f[R] configuration option.
.PP
For example a file like this:
.IP
.EX
\-\-\-
direction: Vertical
parts:
    \- direction: Horizontal
      split_size:
        Percent: 50
      parts:
        \- direction: Vertical
          split_size:
            Percent: 50
        \- direction: Vertical
          split_size:
            Percent: 50
    \- direction: Horizontal
      split_size:
        Percent: 50
.EE
.PP
will tell VC Frame to create this layout:
.IP
.EX
┌─────┬─────┐
│     │     │
├─────┤     │
│     │     │
└─────┴─────┘
.EE
.SS CREATING LAYOUTS
A layout file is a nested tree structure.
Each node describes either a pane (leaf), or a space in which its parts
(children) will be created.
.PP
Each node has following fields: * \f[B]direction: <Horizontal /
Vertical>\f[R] \- node\[cq]s children will be created by a split in
given direction.
* \f[B]split_size:\f[R] \- this indicates either a percentage of the
node\[cq]s parent\[cq]s space or a fixed size of columns/rows from its
parent\[cq]s space.
* \f[B]Percent: <1\-100>\f[R] * \f[B]Fixed:
<lines_number/columns_number>\f[R] * \f[B]plugin:
/path/to/plugin.wasm\f[R] \- optional path to a compiled VC Frame
plugin.
If indicated loads a plugin into the created space.
For more information see PLUGINS section.
* \f[B]default_fg: <color>\f[R] \- set the default foreground color for
a pane (e.g.\ \f[CR]\[dq]#00e000\[dq]\f[R]).
* \f[B]default_bg: <color>\f[R] \- set the default background color for
a pane (e.g.\ \f[CR]\[dq]#001a3a\[dq]\f[R]).
.SH KEYBINDINGS
VC Frame comes with a default set of keybindings which aims to fit as
many users as possible but that behaviour can be overridden or modified
in user configuration files.
The information about bindings is available in the \f[I]keybinds\f[R]
section of configuration.
For example, to introduce a keybinding that will create a new tab and go
to tab 1 after pressing `c' one can write:
.IP
.EX
keybinds:
    normal:
        \- action: [ NewTab, GoToTab: 1,]
          key: [ Char: \[aq]c\[aq],]
.EE
.PP
where \[lq]normal\[rq] stands for a mode name (see MODES section),
\[lq]action\[rq] part specifies the actions to be executed by VC Frame
(see ACTIONS section) and \[lq]key\[rq] is used to list keys or key
combinations bound to given actions (see KEYS).
.PP
The default keybinds can be unbound either for a specific mode, or for
every mode.
It supports either a list of \f[CR]keybinds\f[R], or a bool indicating
that every keybind should be unbound:
.IP
.EX
keybinds:
    unbind: true
.EE
.PP
Will unbind every default binding.
.IP
.EX
keybinds:
    unbind: [ Ctrl: \[aq]p\[aq]]
.EE
.PP
Will unbind every default \f[CR]\[ha]P\f[R] binding for each mode.
.IP
.EX
keybinds:
    normal:
        \- unbind: true
.EE
.PP
Will unbind every default keybind for the \f[CR]normal\f[R] mode.
.IP
.EX
keybinds:
    normal:
        \- unbind: [ Alt: \[aq]n\[aq], Ctrl: \[aq]g\[aq]]
.EE
.PP
Will unbind every default keybind for \f[CR]n\f[R] and \f[CR]\[ha]g\f[R]
for the \f[CR]normal\f[R] mode.
.SS ACTIONS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Quit\f[R] \- quits Zellij
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]SwitchToMode: <InputMode>\f[R] \- switches to the specified input
mode.
See MODES section for possible values.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Resize: <Direction>\f[R] \- resizes focused pane in the specified
direction (one of: Left, Right, Up, Down).
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]FocusNextPane\f[R] \- switches focus to the next pane to the right
or below if on screen edge.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]FocusPreviousPane\f[R] \- switches focus to the next pane to the
left or above if on screen edge.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]SwitchFocus\f[R] \- left for legacy support.
Switches focus to a pane with the next ID.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]MoveFocus: <Direction>\f[R] \- moves focus in the specified
direction (Left, Right, Up, Down).
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Clear\f[R] \- clears current screen.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]DumpScreen: [File] [\[en]pane\-id <ID>]\f[R] \- dumps the pane
content to a file or STDOUT.
If a file path is provided, writes the content to that file.
If omitted, prints the content to STDOUT.
If \[en]pane\-id is provided, dumps the specified pane; otherwise dumps
the focused pane.
<ID> can be a bare integer (eg.
1), a terminal pane id (eg.
terminal_1) or a plugin pane id (eg.
plugin_1).
A bare integer is equivalent to a terminal pane id with the same number.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]DumpLayout: <File>\f[R] \- dumps the screen in the specified or
default file.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]EditScrollback\f[R] \- replaces the current pane with the
scrollback buffer.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]ScrollUp\f[R] \- scrolls up 1 line in the focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]ScrollDown\f[R] \- scrolls down 1 line in the focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]PageScrollUp\f[R] \- scrolls up 1 page in the focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]PageScrollDown\f[R] \- scrolls down 1 page in the focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]ToggleFocusFullscreen\f[R] \- toggles between fullscreen focus pane
and normal layout.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]NewPane: <Direction>\f[R] \- opens a new pane in the specified
direction (Left, Right, Up, Down) relative to focus.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]CloseFocus\f[R] \- closes focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]NewTab\f[R] \- creates a new tab.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]GoToNextTab\f[R] \- goes to the next tab.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]GoToPreviousTab\f[R] \- goes to previous tab.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]CloseTab\f[R] \- closes current tab.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]GoToTab: <Index>\f[R] \- goes to the tab with the specified index
number.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Detach\f[R] \- detach session and exit.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]ToggleActiveSyncTab\f[R] \- toggle between sending text commands to
all panes on the current tab and normal mode.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]UndoRenameTab\f[R] \- undoes the changed tab name and reverts to
the previous name.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]UndoRenamePane\f[R] \- undoes the changed pane name and reverts to
the previous name.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]SetPaneColor\f[R] \- sets the default foreground and/or background
color of a pane.
