.SS MODES
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]normal\f[R] \- the default startup mode of Zellij.
Provides the ability to switch to different modes, as well as some quick
navigation shortcuts.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]locked\f[R] \- disables all keybindings except the one that would
switch the mode to normal (\f[I]ctrl\-g\f[R] by default).
Useful when Zellij\[cq]s keybindings conflict with those of a chosen
terminal app.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]tmux\f[R] \- provides convenience keybindings emulating simple tmux
behaviour
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]pane\f[R] \- includes instructions that manipulate the panes
(adding new panes, moving, closing).
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]tab\f[R] \- includes instructions that manipulate the tabs (adding
new tabs, moving, closing).
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]resize\f[R] \- allows resizing of the focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]scroll\f[R] \- allows scrolling within the focused pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]renametab\f[R] \- is a \[lq]hidden\[rq] mode that can be passed to
\f[I]SwitchToMode\f[R] action.
It will trigger renaming of a tab.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]renamepane\f[R] \- is a \[lq]hidden\[rq] mode that can be passed to
\f[I]SwitchToMode\f[R] action.
It will trigger renaming of a pane.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]session\f[R] \- allows detaching from a session.
.SH Theme
A color theme can be defined either in truecolor, 256 or hex color
format.
Truecolor:
.IP
.EX
fg: [0, 0, 0]
.EE
.PP
256:
.IP
.EX
fg: 0
.EE
.PP
Hex color:
.IP
.EX
fg: \[dq]#000000\[dq]
bg: \[dq]#000\[dq]
.EE
.PP
The color theme can be specified in the following way:
.IP
.EX
themes:
  default:
    fg: [0,0,0]
    bg: [0,0,0]
    black: [0,0,0]
    red: [0,0,0]
    green: [0,0,0]
    yellow: [0,0,0]
    blue: [0,0,0]
    magenta: [0,0,0]
    cyan: [0,0,0]
    white: [0,0,0]
    orange: [0,0,0]
.EE
.PP
If the theme is called \f[CR]default\f[R], then zellij will pick it on
startup.
To specify a different theme, run zellij with:
.IP
.EX
zellij options \-\-theme [NAME]
.EE
.PP
or put the name in the configuration file with \f[CR]theme: [NAME]\f[R].
.SH PLUGINS
Zellij has a plugin system based on WebAssembly.
Any language that can run on WASI can be used to develop a plugin.
To load a plugin include it in a layout file.
Zellij comes with default plugins included: \f[I]status\-bar\f[R],
\f[I]strider\f[R], \f[I]tab\-bar\f[R].
.SH FILES
Default user configuration directory location: * Linux:
\f[I]$XDG_HOME/zellij /home/alice/.config/zellij\f[R] * macOS:
\f[I]/Users/Alice/Library/Application
Support/com.Zellij\-Contributors.zellij\f[R]
.PP
Default user layout directory location: * Subdirectory called
\f[CR]layouts\f[R] inside of the configuration directory.
* Linux: \f[I]$XDG_HOME/zellij/layouts
/home/alice/.config/zellij/layouts * macOS:
\f[R]/Users/Alice/Library/Application/layouts
Support/com.Zellij\-Contributors.zellij/layouts_
.PP
Default plugin directory location: * Linux:
_$XDG_DATA_HOME/zellij/plugins /home/alice/.local/share/plugins
.SH ENVIRONMENT
ZELLIJ_CONFIG_FILE Path of Zellij config to load.
ZELLIJ_CONFIG_DIR Path of the Zellij config directory.
